During systematic zoological investigations conducted by the Hungarian National History Museum in Albania, J. Kontschán, Z. Fehér and D. Murányi also collected, in October, 2004, several nematode samples, and offered them for study to the present author. The nematodes, mostly soil dwellers but with some aquatic species, originated from two districts, Mat and Tiranë in Central Albania on the one hand, and three districts, Tepelenë, Gjirokastër and Delvinë, in South Albania on the other (
Fig. 1
). The majority of them were sampled in mountainous regions.
